"{\"uid\": \"si.com-olympics-legend-katie-ledecky-most-gold-medals-paris-olympics-swimming\", \"noun_phrases\": [{\"sentence\": \"PARIS \\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094 Twelve years as a superstar athlete is an eternity, and in the United States, a shelf life that long usually comes with some level of public blowback or fatigue.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 171, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 73, \"end\": 86, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"score\": 0.9999977388932263, \"rank\": 2.2611037994430158e-06, \"text\": \"United States\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"PARIS \\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 9}, {\"ngram\": \"a superstar athlete\", \"from\": 26, \"to\": 45}, {\"ngram\": \"an eternity\", \"from\": 49, \"to\": 60}, {\"ngram\": \"a shelf life\", \"from\": 88, \"to\": 100}, {\"ngram\": \"some level\", \"from\": 130, \"to\": 140}, {\"ngram\": \"public blowback\", \"from\": 144, \"to\": 159}, {\"ngram\": \"fatigue\", \"from\": 163, \"to\": 170}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Haters materialize to find flaws, inventing them if necessary.\", \"from\": 172, \"to\": 234, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Haters\", \"from\": 172, \"to\": 178}, {\"ngram\": \"flaws\", \"from\": 199, \"to\": 204}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Or the superstar can find ways to self-sabotage, fame warping perspective.\", \"from\": 235, \"to\": 309, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the superstar\", \"from\": 238, \"to\": 251}, {\"ngram\": \"ways\", \"from\": 261, \"to\": 265}, {\"ngram\": \"self-sabotage\", \"from\": 269, \"to\": 282}, {\"ngram\": \"fame warping perspective\", \"from\": 284, \"to\": 308}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Katie Ledecky has experienced none of that in a transcendent career from age 15 to 27.\", \"from\": 311, \"to\": 397, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 311, \"end\": 324, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katie_Ledecky\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Katie Ledecky\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katie_Ledecky\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katie_Ledecky\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"none\", \"from\": 341, \"to\": 345}, {\"ngram\": \"a transcendent career\", \"from\": 357, \"to\": 378}, {\"ngram\": \"age\", \"from\": 384, \"to\": 387}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She keeps swimming and winning.\", \"from\": 398, \"to\": 429, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"We keep cheering.\", \"from\": 430, \"to\": 447, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"There is nothing not to like and respect.\", \"from\": 448, \"to\": 489, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"nothing\", \"from\": 457, \"to\": 464}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She is the greatest female swimmer in history, and has built a case to be considered the best female Olympian in any sport.\", \"from\": 491, \"to\": 614, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 592, \"end\": 600, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\", \"score\": 0.9999999996816769, \"rank\": 3.1811028553695093e-10, \"text\": \"Olympian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the greatest female swimmer\", \"from\": 498, \"to\": 525}, {\"ngram\": \"history\", \"from\": 529, \"to\": 536}, {\"ngram\": \"a case\", \"from\": 552, \"to\": 558}, {\"ngram\": \"any sport\", \"from\": 604, \"to\": 613}]}, {\"sentence\": \"While doing so she has remained cherished, revered and beloved.\", \"from\": 615, \"to\": 678, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"If any athlete has a 100% approval rating in our fractious country, it\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s Ledecky.\", \"from\": 679, \"to\": 762, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"any athlete\", \"from\": 682, \"to\": 693}, {\"ngram\": \"a 100% approval rating\", \"from\": 698, \"to\": 720}, {\"ngram\": \"our fractious country\", \"from\": 724, \"to\": 745}]}, {\"sentence\": \"There\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s just no material for the haters.\", \"from\": 764, \"to\": 806, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"just no material\", \"from\": 774, \"to\": 790}, {\"ngram\": \"the haters\", \"from\": 795, \"to\": 805}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And Ledecky has done nothing to derail herself the way some swimmers have.\", \"from\": 807, \"to\": 881, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Ledecky\", \"from\": 811, \"to\": 818}, {\"ngram\": \"nothing\", \"from\": 828, \"to\": 835}, {\"ngram\": \"some swimmers\", \"from\": 862, \"to\": 875}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Her life is devoid of drama and controversy.\", \"from\": 882, \"to\": 926, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Her life\", \"from\": 882, \"to\": 890}, {\"ngram\": \"drama\", \"from\": 904, \"to\": 909}, {\"ngram\": \"controversy\", \"from\": 914, \"to\": 925}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s the best we have, and everyone loves her.\", \"from\": 927, \"to\": 976, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"She\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s\", \"from\": 927, \"to\": 934}, {\"ngram\": \"everyone\", \"from\": 957, \"to\": 965}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Even the people she beats.\", \"from\": 977, \"to\": 1003, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Even the people\", \"from\": 977, \"to\": 992}]}, {\"sentence\": \"That, as much as 14 total Olympic medals and nine golds, is her legacy-in-the-making.\", \"from\": 1005, \"to\": 1090, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \", as much as 14 total Olympic medals\", \"from\": 1009, \"to\": 1045}, {\"ngram\": \"nine golds\", \"from\": 1050, \"to\": 1060}, {\"ngram\": \"the-making\", \"from\": 1079, \"to\": 1089}]}, {\"sentence\": \"(She\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s not done yet, so stand by.)\", \"from\": 1091, \"to\": 1127, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"She\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s\", \"from\": 1092, \"to\": 1099}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But we would be remiss not to take a moment and talk about all that hardware.\", \"from\": 1128, \"to\": 1205, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a moment\", \"from\": 1163, \"to\": 1171}, {\"ngram\": \"all that hardware\", \"from\": 1187, \"to\": 1204}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Only Michael Phelps has won more gold medals.\", \"from\": 1207, \"to\": 1252, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1212, \"end\": 1226, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michael_Phelps\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.1739136881542064e-98, \"text\": \"Michael Phelps\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michael_Phelps\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michael_Phelps\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"more gold medals\", \"from\": 1235, \"to\": 1251}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Only two Summer Olympians have won more total medals.\", \"from\": 1253, \"to\": 1306, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Only two Summer Olympians\", \"from\": 1253, \"to\": 1278}, {\"ngram\": \"more total medals\", \"from\": 1288, \"to\": 1305}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Ledecky\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s four-peat Saturday night in the 800-meter freestyle\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094with victories in the event in 2012, \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009916, \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009921 and now \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009924\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094ties Phelps as the only swimmers to win the same event in four straight Olympics.\\u00c2 It should be noted that Phelps actually shared domination of the 200 individual medley with Ryan Lochte, who set and still holds the world record in that event.\", \"from\": 1307, \"to\": 1683, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1547, \"end\": 1553, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/William_H._Phelps_Sr.\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.099511060107961e-14, \"text\": \"Phelps\", \"types\": [\"Q901\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/William_H._Phelps_Sr.\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/William_H._Phelps_Sr.\"}, {\"begin\": 1615, \"end\": 1626, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ryan_Lochte\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Ryan Lochte\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ryan_Lochte\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ryan_Lochte\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Ledecky\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s four-peat Saturday night\", \"from\": 1307, \"to\": 1343}, {\"ngram\": \"the 800-meter freestyle\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094with victories\", \"from\": 1347, \"to\": 1387}, {\"ngram\": \"the event\", \"from\": 1391, \"to\": 1400}, {\"ngram\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009916\", \"from\": 1410, \"to\": 1415}, {\"ngram\": \"Phelps\", \"from\": 1444, \"to\": 1450}, {\"ngram\": \"the only swimmers\", \"from\": 1454, \"to\": 1471}, {\"ngram\": \"the same event\", \"from\": 1479, \"to\": 1493}, {\"ngram\": \"four straight Olympics\", \"from\": 1497, \"to\": 1519}, {\"ngram\": \"\\u00c2\", \"from\": 1520, \"to\": 1521}, {\"ngram\": \"domination\", \"from\": 1569, \"to\": 1579}, {\"ngram\": \"the 200 individual medley\", \"from\": 1583, \"to\": 1608}, {\"ngram\": \"the world record\", \"from\": 1651, \"to\": 1667}, {\"ngram\": \"that event\", \"from\": 1671, \"to\": 1681}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Ledecky remains utterly without peer in both the 800 and 1,500.\", \"from\": 1684, \"to\": 1747, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Ledecky\", \"from\": 1684, \"to\": 1691}, {\"ngram\": \"peer\", \"from\": 1716, \"to\": 1720}]}, {\"sentence\": \"(She would have two more gold medals to her name if the Olympics had the latter race for women before 2021.)\", \"from\": 1748, \"to\": 1856, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"two more gold medals\", \"from\": 1764, \"to\": 1784}, {\"ngram\": \"her name\", \"from\": 1788, \"to\": 1796}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 1800, \"to\": 1812}, {\"ngram\": \"the latter race\", \"from\": 1817, \"to\": 1832}, {\"ngram\": \"women\", \"from\": 1837, \"to\": 1842}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This fourth 800 gold was the most challenging.\", \"from\": 1858, \"to\": 1904, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"This fourth 800 gold\", \"from\": 1858, \"to\": 1878}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Australia\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s Ariarne Titmus, who was 11 years old watching Ledecky win her first 800-meter title on TV, has arisen as a worthy rival in the race\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094and as Ledecky\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s superior in the 400.\", \"from\": 1905, \"to\": 2092, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1919, \"end\": 1933, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ariarne_Titmus\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Ariarne Titmus\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ariarne_Titmus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ariarne_Titmus\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Ledecky\", \"from\": 1965, \"to\": 1972}, {\"ngram\": \"her first 800-meter title\", \"from\": 1977, \"to\": 2002}, {\"ngram\": \"TV\", \"from\": 2006, \"to\": 2008}, {\"ngram\": \"a worthy rival\", \"from\": 2024, \"to\": 2038}, {\"ngram\": \"the race\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094and\", \"from\": 2042, \"to\": 2056}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Prior to Titmus, Ledecky won her first Olympic 800 by 4.13 seconds and her second by a preposterous 11.38; the last two have been competitive.\", \"from\": 2093, \"to\": 2235, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2102, \"end\": 2108, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fred_Titmus\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Titmus\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fred_Titmus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fred_Titmus\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Ledecky\", \"from\": 2110, \"to\": 2117}, {\"ngram\": \"her first Olympic\", \"from\": 2122, \"to\": 2139}, {\"ngram\": \"4.13 seconds\", \"from\": 2147, \"to\": 2159}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Ledecky\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s margin of victory in Tokyo three years ago was 1.26 seconds.\", \"from\": 2237, \"to\": 2309, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2270, \"end\": 2275, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.9999967481178951, \"rank\": 3.251891775450489e-06, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Ledecky\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s margin\", \"from\": 2237, \"to\": 2255}, {\"ngram\": \"victory\", \"from\": 2259, \"to\": 2266}, {\"ngram\": \"1.26 seconds\", \"from\": 2296, \"to\": 2308}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Saturday it was 1.25, with Titmus in uncomfortably close stalking range for the first 500 meters.\", \"from\": 2310, \"to\": 2407, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2337, \"end\": 2343, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fred_Titmus\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Titmus\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fred_Titmus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fred_Titmus\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"uncomfortably close stalking range\", \"from\": 2347, \"to\": 2381}, {\"ngram\": \"the first 500 meters\", \"from\": 2386, \"to\": 2406}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Finally, in the 12th and 13th laps of the race, Ledecky cracked it open just enough\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094a .32 advantage on one tape, then .56 on the next\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094and Titmus could not respond.\", \"from\": 2408, \"to\": 2575, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2550, \"end\": 2556, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fred_Titmus\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Titmus\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fred_Titmus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fred_Titmus\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the 12th and 13th laps\", \"from\": 2420, \"to\": 2442}, {\"ngram\": \"the race\", \"from\": 2446, \"to\": 2454}, {\"ngram\": \"Ledecky\", \"from\": 2456, \"to\": 2463}, {\"ngram\": \"just enough\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094a .32 advantage\", \"from\": 2480, \"to\": 2509}, {\"ngram\": \"one tape\", \"from\": 2513, \"to\": 2521}]}, {\"sentence\": \"At that point, Ledecky\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s family\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094parents Mary Gen and Dave, brother Michael, aunts and uncles\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094finally let loose their tightly crossed arms and started cheering Katie home.\", \"from\": 2577, \"to\": 2753, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2621, \"end\": 2625, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mary_Shelley\", \"score\": 0.9981043982387495, \"rank\": 0.0018985733863711625, \"text\": \"Mary\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q36180\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mary_Shelley\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mary_Shelley\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"that point\", \"from\": 2580, \"to\": 2590}, {\"ngram\": \"Dave\", \"from\": 2634, \"to\": 2638}, {\"ngram\": \"brother Michael\", \"from\": 2640, \"to\": 2655}, {\"ngram\": \"aunts\", \"from\": 2657, \"to\": 2662}, {\"ngram\": \"their tightly crossed arms\", \"from\": 2694, \"to\": 2720}, {\"ngram\": \"Katie home\", \"from\": 2742, \"to\": 2752}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Ledecky just had to finish, to a rising crescendo of noise.\", \"from\": 2754, \"to\": 2813, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Ledecky\", \"from\": 2754, \"to\": 2761}, {\"ngram\": \"a rising crescendo\", \"from\": 2785, \"to\": 2803}, {\"ngram\": \"noise\", \"from\": 2807, \"to\": 2812}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Her international approval rating might be as high as it is domestically, with the French crowd at La D\\u00c3\\u00a9fense Arena urging her on passionately.\", \"from\": 2814, \"to\": 2958, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2897, \"end\": 2903, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.5944143650922322, \"rank\": 0.656098479395861, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Her international approval rating\", \"from\": 2814, \"to\": 2847}, {\"ngram\": \"La D\\u00c3\\u00a9fense Arena\", \"from\": 2913, \"to\": 2930}]}, {\"sentence\": \"When Ledecky hit the wall, she threw her head back in relief.\", \"from\": 2960, \"to\": 3021, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Ledecky\", \"from\": 2965, \"to\": 2972}, {\"ngram\": \"the wall\", \"from\": 2977, \"to\": 2985}, {\"ngram\": \"her head\", \"from\": 2997, \"to\": 3005}, {\"ngram\": \"relief\", \"from\": 3014, \"to\": 3020}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This was a bit different than the water-slapping, roaring Katie after demolishing the field in the 1,500 a few nights earlier.\", \"from\": 3022, \"to\": 3148, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the water-slapping\", \"from\": 3052, \"to\": 3070}, {\"ngram\": \"Katie\", \"from\": 3080, \"to\": 3085}, {\"ngram\": \"the field\", \"from\": 3104, \"to\": 3113}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cI just felt a lot of pressure from myself just from my history in the race,\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d Ledecky said.\", \"from\": 3150, \"to\": 3245, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a lot\", \"from\": 3165, \"to\": 3170}, {\"ngram\": \"pressure\", \"from\": 3174, \"to\": 3182}, {\"ngram\": \"my history\", \"from\": 3205, \"to\": 3215}, {\"ngram\": \"the race\", \"from\": 3219, \"to\": 3227}, {\"ngram\": \"Ledecky\", \"from\": 3232, \"to\": 3239}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cAnd I knew going into it that it was going to be a really tough race and that everyone i